Semantics of Programming Languages

http://fsl.cs.illinois.edu/index.php/Semantics_of_Programming_Languages

One of the most effective ways to define a programming language or paradigm is as an executable formal specification.
This has at least two advantages:

(1) one can execute programs, and
(2) one can formally reason about programs and programming languages.

